> the biggest problems that i have with butt splice crimps has to do with
> installation and volume requirements.  

I *do* use them because they're cheap. BUT! I either shrink tube them,
or use brush on stuff. PLUS: I also provide strain relief by zip tying
both wires together a few inches away from the connector. If I have
the slop that is. If not, I just hope there's no good tugs on the
connector...

